1)Command to create new directory
Command: hdfs dfs -mkdir -p  /home/osboxes/new

2)Command to list the files in directory
Command: hdfs dfs -ls [-d][-h][-R] /

3)Command to create the file 
Command: hdfs dfs -touchz /home/osboxes/new/file1.txt

4)HDFS Command to check the health of the Hadoop file system.
Command: hdfs fsck /

5)Command to check the file size 
Command: hdfs dfs -du -s <path>

6)Command to view the file 
Command: hdfs dfs -cat <file1>

7)Command to remove the file 
Command : hdfs dfs -rm /home/osboxes/new2/file2.txt

8)Command to cp the files 
Command : hdfs dfs -cp <path1> <path2>

9)Command that makes the trash empty.
Command: hdfs dfs -expunge

10) Command that returns the help for an individual command.
Usage: hdfs dfs -usage <command>
Command: hdfs dfs -usage mkdir

11)Command to change the replication factor of file 
Command : hdfs dfs -setrep -w 3 /user/dataflair/dir1 ? when the path is dire? what if already files are present will it change its also?

12)Command to  copy file from local to hdfs
Command :hadoop fs -copyFromLocal /home/osboxes/sample.txt hdfs://localhost:9000

13)hadoop fs -rm -r <path> To remove directory recursively 

14)hadoop fs -test <options> To test various conditions

15) Hadoop command to list the files in local
Command : hadoop fs -ls file:///home/osboxes/sample.txt

16) Command to view the hadoop supported compressed data
hadoop fs -text file:///home/osboxes/sample.txt.gz






